column5: Bill, don't forget to bring your computer to Lac Seul when you go in a few days as the WC community very much enjoys reading your live reports!!!!!Don't forget the jigs!!!!

BigtimeelectricGoing to pack the mlap top tomorrow.I'll post on WC as often as I can.I packed some maps I can mark and leave with Doug for your arrival.I'm taking a break from packing fishing tackle.I'm almost ready to go.Lucy says "Hi".Bill
Will you leave some in cabin 3 at Onaway as well. Just put in a sealed container marked SinOrSwim. Maybe also mark "Urine Sample" on the outside so nobody else opens it.

Sin or SwimWhen will you be there? Nothing will be left for "urine testing".The last time I had a UA it said and I quote" your horse has diabetes". Bigtime AKA "Mark" and his crew me with Lucy and I at Gawley's.That's how my wife and I discover Little Beaver Lodge.We also met on the lake at a "spot or two". Sin if you want a map,marked let me know.May your bottom bouncer just tick the bottom and your rod load up with a big un'.Bill
Would absolutely love a marked map. Let me know. PM me. Thanks!We will be there early September. Finding humps and stuff on a lake that big is difficult.
Bill, make sure not to give that sinner anything west south or north of bay of islands.....lol
I can see it now. He will grab a map, throw a couple darts at it and mark "HUGE Walleye" on those spots. LOL
Just as long as he doesn't leave a map marked with "ran new boat up on rocks" here,,,,,, HRG
